cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NI 

This paper deals with the robustness of Deep Learning models used for IoT malware classification against Adversarial Learning attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of graph-based models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with IoT malware, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
